 Navistar International Logo
Navistar International Corporation is an American holding company created in 1986 as the successor to International Harvester. Navistar operates as the owner of International brand of trucks and diesel engines. The company also produces military vehicles through its Navistar Defense subsidiary along with bus production through IC Bus. Currently, Traton SE is the largest stakeholder of Navistar, owning 17% of the company. Headquartered in Lisle, Illinois, the company has 13,000 employees worldwide as of 2019.
